<h1>Mark Hermann</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://rockandrollzen.com/now/">rockandrollzen.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
New York
NY
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Music producer, songwriter, guitar player, brand music specialist, writer, blogger, av systems designer.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I'm a storyteller who helps inspire other creators to dig down, find their truth and share their unique story with the world so we all can benefit from sharing our gift with the world.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I tell stories to inspire and connect us to our shared humanity.  I play music because there is no greater connection to our hearts. I help stuck creators to find their truth so they can share their gift with the world
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
That the way to overcome failure or to get through a difficult situation is to ask the question, “What's great about this?” Though the immediate thought may be that nothing is great and that this moment sucks, the answer will finally reveal itself, thus turning that failure into a powerful lesson.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"The Alchemist" by Paulo Coelho
</p>

